com.github.dandelion.datatables.core.extension

Class AbstractExtension

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.dandelion.datatables.core.extension.AbstractExtension
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Extension
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractFilteringFeature, AjaxFeature, AjaxReloadFeature, AppearFeature, Bootstrap2Theme, Bootstrap3Theme, ColReorderPlugin, ExportFeature, ExternalFilterFeature, ExtraHtmlFeature, ExtraJsFeature, FixedHeaderPlugin, JQueryUITheme, PagingTypeBootstrapFullFeature, PagingTypeBootstrapFullNumbersFeature, PagingTypeBootstrapSimpleFeature, PagingTypeExtJsFeature, PagingTypeInputFeature, PagingTypeListboxFeature, PagingTypeScrollingFeature, PipeliningFeature, ResponsivePlugin, ScrollerPlugin, ServerSideFeature, SortingFeature

    public abstract class AbstractExtension
extends Object
implements Extension

    Abstract superclass for all extensions.

    Lots of utilities are available in this class, allowing you to:

    • bufferize Javascript code, at different location, before flushing it in the final TODO
    • add some Parameter to the generated DataTables configuration, thanks to addParameter(Parameter), addParameter(String, Object) and #addParameter(String, Object, Mode) methods
    • add some bundles to the current request
    • add some Callback to the generated DataTables configuration

    Also note that you can access the Dandelion Context using the getContext().

    In order to use the extension mechanism, you should:

    1. Create a class that extends AbstractExtension. You could directly create a class that directly implements Extension but this is not recommended.
    2. Create a file called com.github.dandelion.datatables.core.extension.Extension under the META-INF/services folder: 
       META - INF / services / com.github.dandelion.datatables.core.extension.Extension
    3. Add to the above file the full qualified name of your extension class.
      For example, assuming the following extension class: 
       package com.company.extension;
 
 public class MyExtension extends AbstractExtension {
    ...
 }
      The file com.github.dandelion.datatables.core.extension.Extension should contain: 
       com.company.extension.MyExtension
    Note that if you wish to override an already existing extension, you shouldn't override the Extension.getExtensionName() method.
    Since:
    0.7.1
    Author:
    Thibault Duchateau

      • addCallback

        public void addCallback(CallbackType callbackType,
               String javascript)

        Adds a Callback to the DataTables generated configuration.

        By default, if the CallbackType already exists in the configuration, the code will be appended to the existing code.

        Parameters:
        callbackType - The type of the callback.
        javascript - The Javascript code to execute in the callback.

        javascript - The Javascript code to execute in the callback.
